Pumpkin Oatmeal Breakfast Bars Recipe 
Ingredients 
1½ c. whole rolled oats (certified gluten free if needed for an allergy) 
½ c. nuts (pecan and walnuts are both excellent!) 
1 tsp. vanilla 
¾ c. pumpkin puree 
1 egg 
1 very ripe (small) banana 
2 Tbs. maple syrup or honey 
1 tsp. cinnamon 
½ tsp. ginger 
¼ tsp. cardamom (optional) 
Instructions 
Use a fork to mash the banana into a smooth paste in a medium size mixing bowl. 
Add the vanilla, pumpkin, egg and maple syrup or honey and stir until smooth. 
Add the oats, nuts, and spices and stir just until combined. 
Pour into a well greased 8x8 baking dish or pie plate. Use a rubber spatula to smooth the batter out to the edges of the pan. 
Bake at 350 degrees for about 20-25 min. 
Note: If the mixture seems very runny, feel free to add more oats to thicken up before baking. The moisture content of your pumpkin and size of banana have a big impact here. 

START RECIPE


Cardamom Ginger Peach Crumble Recipe (Gluten-Free) 
Ingredients 
Filling: 
8 peaches, sliced and peeled 
¼ tsp. ginger 
1 tsp. cinnamon 
¾ tsp. cardamom 
2-3 Tbs. flour (oat or whole wheat) 
1-2 Tbs. cane sugar, rapadura, or sucanat 
2 Tbs. crystallized ginger 
½ c. chopped pecans (optional) 
Topping: 
1 cup rolled oats 
½ cup flour (oat of whole wheat) 
¾ c. butter 
¼ c. cane sugar, rapadura, or sucanat 
2 tsp. vanilla 
1 tsp. cinnamon 
Instructions 
Preheat the oven to 350. 
Combine all of the filling ingredients and gently stir to combine. If the peaches are very ripe and juicy use 3 Tbs. flour and only 1 Tbsp. sugar. If the peaches are firm then only use 2 Tbs. flour and increase the sugar to 2 Tbs. 
In another bowl combine the oats, flour and cinnamon. 
Cut the butter into chunks and sprinkle on top of the topping mixture. 
Sprinkle the vanilla on top of the butter and mash everything together with a fork. 
Spread the fruit mixture into an 8x8 pan, a deep pie plate or individual ramekins. 
Sprinkle the topping over the fruit, gently pressing down as you go. 
Bake for 20-25 minutes or until the fruit is bubbly and the topping is golden brown. 
Serve warm or cold. 

