Roasted Strawberries with Vanilla Bean 
Roasted Strawberries with Vanilla Bean 

Ina Garten is a genius!!! Seriously, every recipe I’ve ever tried of hers is amazing. I had some strawberries and decided to try roasting them. I remember seeing a recipe awhile back that Ina had for roasting berries with vanilla bean seeds. I decided to adapt the recipe a bit by just using the strawberries I had on hand. The berries smelled incredible while they roasted. After sampling them, I couldn’t get over how much flavor the vanilla bean seeds added to the strawberries. My kids had these berries over vanilla ice cream for dessert and over waffles for breakfast. They absolutely LOVED them! I’ll be roasting berries like this from now on!!! 

Roasted Strawberries with Vanilla Bean 

Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Coat a baking dish with cooking spray. 

Place the strawberries in the prepared baking dish and toss with the sugar and vanilla bean seeds (click here to see instructions on seed removal). 

Roasted Strawberries with Vanilla Bean 

Place into the oven and roast in the oven for 20 minutes. Cool to room temperature before serving. Great plain or on yogurt, ice cream, pancakes, or waffles. Enjoy. 

