START RECIPE

Skillet Huevos Rancheros 
Skillet Huevos Rancheros 

This was a perfect Sunday morning breakfast. I sautйed some onion then added drained black beans along with some seasonings and enchilada sauce. I layered a small cast iron skillet with a corn tortilla topped with the black bean mixture then cracked a couple of eggs on top along with some tomato. I baked it until the egg whites were cooked through but the yolks were still runny. I topped it with cotija cheese, bits of diced jalapeno, and fresh cilantro. I served these huevos rancheros with spicy salsa and lime wedges. My husband loved it and so did I. 

Skillet Huevos Rancheros 

Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Coat a small cast iron pan with cooking spray. 

Heat the oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and sautй for 3-5 minutes or until softened. Add the rinsed and drained black beans to the skillet along with the enchilada sauce. Season with a couple dashes of oregano, coriander, cumin, garlic powder, sea salt, and freshly cracked pepper, to taste. Cook for 3-5 minutes. Remove from heat. 

Heat the tortilla over a gas flame on both sides for 20-30 seconds OR heat in a microwave for 10 seconds, or until pliable. Place the tortilla in the bottom of the prepared cast iron skillet. 

Skillet Huevos Rancheros 

Spoon some of the black bean mixture on top of the tortilla. Crack one or two eggs in the center. Sprinkle a few diced tomatoes on top. 

Place into the oven and cook for 10-12 minutes or until the whites are cooked through but the yolks are still runny. Remove from the oven and top with diced jalapeno, fresh cilantro, and cotija cheese. Serve with salsa and lime wedges on the side. Enjoy! 

Skillet Huevos Rancheros 


 

SKILLET HUEVOS RANCHEROS 
 

Yield: 1Cook Time: 15-20 minutes 
INGREDIENTS: 
1 tsp vegetable oil 
1/4 sweet yellow onion, sliced 
Can of black beans, drained & rinsed 
2-3 tbsp enchilada sauce 
Dash of oregano, to taste 
Dash of coriander, to taste 
Dash of cumin, to taste 
Dash of garlic powder, to taste 
Sea salt and freshly cracked pepper, to taste 
1 corn tortilla 
2 eggs 
3 grape tomatoes, diced 
2 tsp jalapeno, diced 
1 tbsp fresh cilantro 
2 tsp crumbled cotija cheese 
Salsa 
Lime wedges 

DIRECTIONS: 
Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Coat a small cast iron pan with cooking spray. 

Heat the oil in a skillet over medium heat. Add the onion and sautй for 3-5 minutes or until softened. Add the rinsed and drained black beans to the skillet along with the enchilada sauce. Season with a couple dashes of oregano, coriander, cumin, garlic powder, sea salt, and freshly cracked pepper, to taste. Cook for 3-5 minutes. Remove from heat. 

Heat the tortilla over a gas flame on both sides for 20-30 seconds OR heat in a microwave for 10 seconds, or until pliable. Place the tortilla in the bottom of the prepared cast iron skillet. Spoon some of the black bean mixture on top of the tortilla. Crack one or two eggs in the center. Sprinkle a few diced tomatoes on top. 

Place into the oven and cook for 10-12 minutes or until the whites are cooked through but the yolks are still runny. Remove from the oven and top with diced jalapeno, fresh cilantro, and cotija cheese. Serve with salsa and lime wedges on the side. Enjoy! 

Recipe and photos by For the Love of Cooking.net 

START RECIPE

Egg, Ham, and Extra Sharp Cheddar Breakfast Wrap 
Egg, Ham, and Extra Sharp Cheddar Breakfast Wrap 

I was in the mood for something light for lunch. I looked through the refrigerator and grabbed some tortillas, eggs, ham, green onion and cheese. I scrambled up the eggs along with the ham and cheese then rolled them up in a tortilla. A quick and easy lunch that I could eat on the go – perfect for busy days. 

Egg, Ham, and Extra Sharp Cheddar Breakfast Wrap 

Heat a skillet coated with cooking spray over medium heat. Combine the eggs with some sea salt and freshly cracked pepper, to taste. Whisk until smooth. Pour the egg mixture into the hot skillet. Slowly fold the egg mixture from the bottom of the pan to the top. This will keep the eggs from overcooking and the middle section will stay soft and fluffy. Do this constantly for 1 or 2 minutes, or until the eggs are just set.  Add the sliced ham, green onions, and grated cheddar then toss to warm everything. Do not overcook. Remove from heat. 

Heat a flour tortilla in the microwave for a 10-15 seconds, or until warm and pliable. Spoon the egg and ham mixture down the center of the tortilla then roll. Serve immediately. Enjoy. 

Egg, Ham, and Extra Sharp Cheddar Breakfast Wrap 


 

EGG, HAM, AND EXTRA SHARP CHEDDAR BREAKFAST WRAP 
 

Yield: 1 wrapCook Time: 5 minutes 
INGREDIENTS: 
Cooking spray 
2 eggs 
Sea salt and freshly cracked pepper, to taste 
2 slices of Canadian Bacon, chopped 
1-2 tbsp extra sharp cheddar, grated 
2 tsp green onions, chopped 
1 flour tortilla, warmed 
Hot sauce, if desired 

DIRECTIONS: 
Heat a skillet coated with cooking spray over medium heat. Combine the eggs with some sea salt and freshly cracked pepper, to taste. Whisk until smooth. Pour the egg mixture into the hot skillet. Slowly fold the egg mixture from the bottom of the pan to the top. This will keep the eggs from overcooking and the middle section will stay soft and fluffy. Do this constantly for 1 or 2 minutes, or until the eggs are just set. Add the sliced ham, green onions, and grated cheddar then toss to warm everything. Do not overcook. Remove from heat. 

Heat a flour tortilla in the microwave for a 10-15 seconds, or until warm and pliable. Spoon the egg and ham mixture down the center of the tortilla then roll. Serve immediately. Enjoy. 

