THE EASIEST SPINACH LASAGNA 
5 FROM 8 VOTES 
COURSE: MAIN COURSE  PREP TIME: 15 MINUTES  COOK TIME: 55 MINUTES TOTAL TIME: 1 HOUR 10 MINUTES  SERVINGS  (ADJUST TO SUIT):  
6 
Print 
INGREDIENTS 
15 ounces ricotta cheese 
8 ounces mozzarella cheese, grated  
1 cup parmesan cheese, grated and divided 
10 ounces frozen spinach, thawed and squeezed dry (I used Cascadian Farm Organic brand and love that it’s already chopped for me!) 
1 egg 
ј teaspoon salt 
3 cups pasta sauce, 25 ounce jar 
8 ounces whole-wheat lasagna, no-boil 
INSTRUCTIONS  
Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F. 
In a large bowl, mix the ricotta, mozzarella, ѕ cup of the Parmesan, spinach, egg, and salt. 
In a 13 x 9 inch baking dish, spread ѕ cup sauce on the bottom. Layer a few of the noodles on top. Spread a third of the cheese mixture on top of that and then another 3/4 cup sauce. Repeat layers until all ingredients are gone, ending with the sauce. 
Top with remaining ј cup Parmesan, cover with foil, and bake for 30 minutes. Remove foil START RECIPE
and bake for another 20 to 25 minutes or until the noodles have completely softened. Let rest for 5 minutes, serve warm, and enjoy! 
RECIPE NOTES  
We recommend organic ingredients when feasible.  


