Blueberry Buckle 
Blueberry Buckle 

We stayed home and had a quiet Christmas vacation for the first time in a long while and it was wonderful. While it was sad to be away from our far away friends and family, we were also really happy to be home. We had many lazy days, ate good food, played lots of board games, ed a ton of movies, and slept in almost every single day. Other than heading to the beach one day, we stayed close to home and it was just what we all needed. I hope you all had a wonderful holiday break too! 

My kids still have a couple days of vacation left but my husband headed back to work today so I decided to get back to work too. The grocery store had a great sale on blueberries so I grabbed some and decided to do some baking. When looking for a recipe online, I came across a recipe for a blueberry buckle which had me intrigued. A blueberry buckle is basically a dense blueberry cake with a struesel topping that “buckles” as the cake is baking. My kids each had a friend over and they all happily taste tested the cake for me. Thankfully, it was a HUGE hit with all four of them and they said it was delicious. I am looking forward to having a slice for dessert tonight. 

Blueberry Buckle 

Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Coat a round cake pan with cooking spray. delimINGER

In a large bowl, cream together the sugar, butter. Add the egg and lemon zest then beat until fluffy. delimINGER

In a separate bowl combine the flour, baking powder, and salt. Add the flour mixture to the creamed mixture, alternating with the milk. Mix until just combined. delimINGER

Toss blueberries with 1 tablespoon flour. Fold into batter and spread the thick batter in the prepared pan. delimINGER

Blueberry Buckle  

Combine the streusel toppings together with your fingers until crumbly. 

Blueberry Buckle 

Sprinkle the streusel topping over batter evenly and bake 40-50 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. 

Blueberry Buckle 

STEAR RECIPE
PEAR CRANBERRY GINGERSNAP CRUMBLE 
 

SAVE 
 
PRINT 
Prep time  
15 mins 
Cook time 
45 mins 
Total time 
1 hour 
Author: Pam - For the Love Cooking / Original by Smitten Kitchen 
Recipe type: Dessert 
Serves: 8 
INGREDIENTS 

Crumble: delimINGER
1 cup gingersnap, crushed into crumbs delimINGER
1 cup flour delimINGER
ј cup white sugar delimINGER
3 tbsp brown sugar delimINGER
? tsp ground ginger delimINGER
? tsp salt delimINGER
Ѕ cup unsalted butter, melted and cooled delimINGER

Fruit Filling: delimINGER
4 pears, peeled, halved, cored and sliced ј inch thick delimINGER
1Ѕ cups fresh cranberries delimINGER
Ѕ cup granulated sugar delimINGER
2 tbsp cornstarch delimINGER
1 tbsp fresh lemon juice delimINGER
Ѕ tsp lemon zest,finely grated delimINGER
Ѕ tsp vanilla extract delimINGER
INSTRUCTIONS 
Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Coat a large baking dish with cooking spray. Place the baking dish on a tin foil lined baking sheet. 
Stir together the crushed gingersnaps, flour, granulated sugar, brown sugar, ginger and salt.
Add the melted butter and stir until large crumbs form. Set aside. 
Mix the sliced pears, cranberries, sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice, lemon zest and vanilla together in the large baking dish (instead of getting another bowl dirty). 
Sprinkle the gingersnap crumble over the fruit mixture. 
