2    Cover: cook on Low heat setting 8 to 9 hours or until very tender. Remove pork from slow cooker: when cool enough to handle, shred pork with fork. Remove 1 cup cooking liquid: place in large bowl. Add shredded pork to bowl: toss to coat. 
3    Meanwhile, discard remaining cooking liquid: wipe out slow cooker. Spray slow cooker with cooking spray. Add broth, tomatoes and corn: stir in pork. Cover: cook on High heat setting 1 hour 30 minutes to 2 hours 30 minutes or until hot. Serve with remaining ingredients. 

