21 Ratings 
16 Comments 
Key Lime Magic Bars 

Prep 15 min 
Total 1 hr 35 min 
Servings 16 

Greek yogurt lightens up this tasty, tangy twist on traditional magic bars. 
Cindy Rahe 
Ingredients 
9 graham cracker rectangles, crushed to about 1 1/2 cups crumbs 
1/2 cup old-fashioned or quick-cooking oats, coarsely ground 
1/4 cup melted coconut oil (or butter) 
1 tablespoon sugar 
1/4 teaspoon kosher salt 
1/2 cup canned sweetened condensed milk (not evaporated) 
1 container (5.3 oz) Yoplait® Greek 100 protein Key lime yogurt 
2 teaspoons grated lime peel 
1 tablespoon lime juice 
1 1/2 cups shredded unsweetened coconut 
1/2 cup white vanilla baking chips 
Steps 

1    Heat oven to 350° F. Line 8-inch square pan with cooking parchment paper: spray with cooking spray. 
2    In small bowl, stir together graham cracker crumbs, ground oats, melted coconut oil, sugar and salt. Press mixture evenly in bottom of pan. 
3    In medium bowl, beat condensed milk, yogurt, lime peel and lime juice with whisk. Stir in coconut and white chips. Spread mixture over graham cracker base. 
4    Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until set and just golden around edges. Cool completely on cooling rack, about 1 hour. Cut into 4 rows by 4 rows. 

