START RECIPE
Eggnog White Hot Chocolate 
By Andrew Kaplan  •  December 19, 2017 

Eggnog White Hot Chocolate 
Makes 2 cups 
Ingredients 
1 cup heavy cream, optional 
Pinch powdered sugar, optional 
4 oz. white chocolate 
Tiny pinch of salt 
1 cup eggnog 
1 cup milk 
Pinch ground cinnamon 
1-2 shots of whisky or bourbon 
Mini candy canes, for garnish 
Preparation 
Place heavy cream in a stand mixer and whip on high speed. Add a few pinches of powdered sugar and whip until medium or stiff peaks form. If you do not have a stand mixer, you may use a handheld mixer – or if using a whisk, beat by hand. When finished, place in fridge until ready to use. 

Place a small nonstick saucepot or skillet over low heat and add the white chocolate and a tiny pinch of salt. Gently stir with a whisk until melted and then slowly add the eggnog, milk, and cinnamon. Whisk until smooth and incorporated and heated through- no need to boil. If you need an extra umph, and are of age, add a shot of whisky. 

Divide between 2 mugs, place a dollop of whipped cream on top and garnish with a sprinkle of cinnamon and/or a mini candy cane. 

[This recipe is part of a sponsorship with our partner, Trane.] 

DRINKS FEEDBACK 

