By John Cusimano  •  November 28, 2017 

Applesauce Whiskey Sour 
Serves 1 cocktail 
This recipe originally appeared on the Rachael Ray Show. For more recipes and videos from the show visit RachaelRayShow.com. 

Ingredients 
Applesauce from the bottom of the jar 
2 1/2 ounces rye whiskey 
1 ounce lemon juice 
1/2 ounce cinnamon simple syrup (1 part water + 1 part sugar + cinnamon sticks heated until sugar dissolves then cooled) 
Preparation 
To the applesauce jar, add whiskey, lemon juice, simple syrup and some ice. Cover with jar lid, shake and DOUBLE strain with a normal cocktail strainer AND one of those mini cocktail strainers that look like tiny veggie strainers into a chilled coupe. 

