START RECIPE


Sweet-Sour Coleslaw 
Just like grandma used to make! 

Ingredients:  
1½ pounds cabbage, shredded 1/8 thick 
2/3 cup (150 mL) sugar 
1/3 cup (75 mL) white vinegar 
1 tsp (5 mL)  
1 cup (250 mL) 35% whipping cream 
salt and freshly ground black pepper, to taste 

Time:  
Total time: 62 Min 

Yield:  
Serves: 10-12 

Method:  
Place sliced / shredded cabbage in a large bowl. 
Mix sugar, vinegar, and salt in a small bowl. 
Add to cabbage and toss to coat. 
Add cream and toss it again. 
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes before serving. 
Season with salt and pepper: serve. 


START RECIPE


Stout Meatballs with Beer BBQ Sauce 
This is perfect for the big game! What could be better than beef ’n’ beer. 

Ingredients:  
For the meatballs: 
½ lb (250g) ground beef 
½ lb (250g) ground pork 
1 tsp (5 mL) garlic powder 
1 tsp (5 mL) onion powder 
1/4 tsp (1 mL) cumin 
1/4 tsp (1 mL) cayenne pepper 
1/2 tsp (2 mL) salt 
1 egg 
1/4 cup (60 ml) breadcrumbs 
1/4 cup (60 mL) stout beer 

For the sauce: 
1 Tbsp (15 mL) olive oil 
4 cloves garlic, minced 
1 cup (250 mL) stout 
1/3 cup (75 mL) brown sugar 
3 Tbsp (45 ml) tomato paste 
2 Tbsp (30 mL) Worcestershire sauce 
1/3 cup (75 mL) soy sauce 
2 tsp (10 mL) smoked paprika 
1 tsp (5 mL) onion powder 
1 1/2 tsp (7 mL) Sriracha 

Time:  
Total time: 75 Min 

Yield:  
Makes: 28 Meatballs 

Method:  
In a large bowl add all the meatball ingredients, mix with your hands until just combined. Don't overmix! Place in the fridge to chill for 1 hour or up to 1 day. 
While chilling make the sauce.In a pot over medium high heat, add the oil and the garlic: stir and fry for about 30 seconds. 
Add all of the remaining sauce ingredients: stir and simmer until thickened and reduced, about 15 minutes. 

Preheat oven to 400ºF (200ºC).Using a scoop and your hands, form meat balls same size as a pin-pong ball. 
Place on a parchment paper covered cookie sheet. Cook in the preheated oven for 15 minutes. 
Heat 2 Tbsp olive oil in a skillet over medium high heat until hot. 
Add the partially cooked meat balls, and cook until they start to brown. 
Reduce heat and add the sauce, cooking at a simmer until meatballs are glazed and sauce is very thick. 

Makes about 28 meatballs 


START RECIPE

Savoury Stuffed Mushrooms 
This is a fantastic appetiser for a romantic dinner party! 

Ingredients:  
6 large fresh mushrooms 
4½ tsp (22 mL) finely chopped green pepper 
4½ tsp (22 mL) finely chopped onion 
1 Tbsp (15 mL) butter 
3/4 cup (175 mL) day-old bread cut into small cubes 
Pinch salt 
Pinch pepper 
Pinch cayenne pepper 

Time:  
Prep time: 15 Min, 
Cook time: 15 Min, 
Total time: 39 Min 

Yield:  
Makes: 6 

Method:  
Pre-heat oven to 350°F (180ºC) 
Remove stems from mushrooms, set caps aside and finely chop the stems . 
In a skillet, sauté stems, green pepper and onion in butter until tender. 
Remove from the heat, and stir in the cayenne, bread, salt, and pepper. 

Stuff mixture into mushroom caps. 
Place on a baking tray and bake, uncovered for 15 minutes or until stuffing is lightly browned. 


