Caribbean Jerk Seasoning Rub 
People immediately think Hot & Spicy when they think Jamaican jerk rub. That's not always the case, most chefs pride themselves on a flavourful jerk spice mix with very little heat. Too many hot peppers m all of the other flavours... So we give you this jerk rub with no peppers: try it out and add the heat later if you need it. 

Ingredients:  
2 Tbsp (30 mL) brown sugar 
2½ tsp (12 mL) salt 
2 tsp (10 mL) allspice 
1 tsp (5 mL) cayenne pepper 
1 tsp (5 mL) freshly ground black pepper 
1 tsp (5 mL) onion powder 
½ tsp (2 mL) ground cinnamon 
½ tsp (2 mL) garlic powder 
¼ tsp (1 mL) ground cumin 
¼ tsp (1 mL) dried thyme 

Time:  
Prep time: 15 Min, 
Total time: 15 Min 

Yield:  
Makes: 12 

Method:  
Mix all ingredients and store in a cool, dark place. Use within three months. 
Great on: Chicken, pork or fish. 
Just remember to grill over indirect heat, low and slow with a little smoke. 

Tags: allspice  cumin  cinnamon  cayenne 


