Chicken & Rice One-Pot Meal 
Chicken and rice in one pot - easy, fast, tasty weeknight meal! 

Ingredients:  
1 tablespoon (15 mL) olive oil 
2¼ pounds (1.1 Kg) chicken thighs, cut into 2 pieces 
4 Anaheim or poblano chile peppers, chopped 
1 small onion, chopped 
1 tablespoon (15 mL) dried oregano, crushed 
1 teaspoon (5 mL) sweet paprika 
1 teaspoon (5 mL) salt 
1 can (398 mL) tomato sauce 
2 tomatos, chopped 
1 can (1cup) pimientos, rinsed 
Handfull stuffed green olives 
2 tablespoons (30 mL) capers, rinsed 
2 cups (500 mL) water 
4 cups (1L) chicken stock 
2½ cups (625 mL) rice 

Time:  
Prep time: 25 Min, 
Cook time: 50 Min, 
Total time: 75 Min 

Yield:  
Serves: 6 

Method:  
Heat oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat. 
Add chicken, chiles, onion, oregano, paprika and salt and cook, stirring, until the onions have softened, 3 to 5 minutes. 
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, pimientos, olives, capers, water, and stock: bring to a boil. 
Stir in rice: return to a boil then reduce heat to a simmer and cook, uncovered, until the sauce is thick, the rice is tender and the chicken is cooked through, 35 to 45 minutes. 



