Saffron-Yogurt Chicken Kebabs 
  4 
 kebabs saffron yogurt chicken 
Recipe photo courtesy of Bobbi Lin 
A rich Greek yogurt-based marinade is the key to these juicy flame-kissed chicken skewers. Source: Martha Stewart's Cooking School, Episode 508
Serves 4 to 6 
YIELD 

INGREDIENTS 
Ingredients on sale 
Currently these ingredients aren't on sale near you. 
 
3/4 cup plain whole-milk Greek yogurt 
1/4 cup extra-virgin olive oil, plus more for drizzling 
Zest and juice of 1 lemon 
2 tablespoons chopped fresh thyme leaves 
2 cloves garlic, roughly chopped 
1/2 teaspoon saffron threads 
1/2 teaspoon paprika 
1/4 teaspoon ground turmeric 
1/8 teaspoon cayenne pepper 
Kosher salt and freshly ground pepper 
2 pounds boneless, skinless chicken thighs, cut into 2-inch pieces 
6 lemon wedges, for serving 
DIRECTIONS 
1. In a medium bowl, whisk to combine yogurt, oil, lemon zest and juice, thyme, garlic, saffron, paprika, turmeric, cayenne, 2 teaspoons salt, and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. 
2. Add chicken to yogurt marinade and toss to coat. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least 2 hours and up to overnight.
3. Preheat grill or grill pan to medium-high. Thread chicken onto six 10-inch skewers and season with salt and pepper. Grill chicken until cooked through, about 6 to 8 minutes per side. Drizzle with oil and serve with lemon wedges. 
COOK'S NOTES 
If using wooden skewers, soak them in water for 30 minutes before grilling. 


