START RECIPE


JAPCHAE (KOREAN SWEET POTATO NOODLES) 
 your own photos 
What you need:  
1/4 of a bag of dangmyun (Korean Sweet Potato Noodles) 

3 Chinese Mushrooms (pre-soaked for 20 minutes) /Fresh Shitake, stalks removed 

2 stalks of green leafy vegetables, chopped 

1 carrot, sliced 

1 onion, sliced 

2 cloves of garlic, chopped 

1 teaspoon of sesame seeds 

Seasonings 

3 tablespoons of sesame oil 

4 tablespoons of light soy sauce 

1 teaspoon of sugar 

Salt, pepper to taste 

 

What you do:  
1. In a heated wok or pan, stir-fry onions and garlic until fragrant. 

2. Add mushrooms to the wok/pan and continue to stir-fry.  

3. Place the noodles in the wok /pan and stir-fry over high heat, stirring constantly to avoid noodles from sticking to the wok/pan. 

4. Add your favourite leafy vegetables and carrot and stir-fry for 3 to 5 minutes. 

5. Add seasonings and sesame seeds. Combine the ingredients well. 

6. Garnish with parsley (optional) and serve! 

Preparation Time:  
15 minutes 
Cooking Time:  
20 minutes 
Servings:  
