START RECIPE


COUSCOUS SUPREME 

View photos submitted by others |  your own photos 
What you need:  
1/2 cup onions chopped 
2 cloves of garlic chopped 
1 small sweet red pepper chopped 
3 tablespoons sun-dried tomatoes, with oil chopped 
3 cups fresh spinach rinsed well and dried 
1 cup uncooked couscous 
water for couscous (check package) 
2 sprays olive oil cooking spray 
1 tablespoon kosher salt 
fresh ground pepper to taste 

What you do:  
Prepare the couscous according to package directions and set aside. 
Sauté the garlic, onion and red pepper in a pan coated with the olive oil spray until softened. Sprinkle with 1/2 the kosher salt. 
Add the sun-dried tomatoes and mix well to combine. 
Add the spinach. When it is wilted add, the couscous, fresh ground pepper remaining salt and mix well. 
Serving size ½ cup. 
yum! 

Preparation Time:  
20 min 
Cooking Time:  
Servings:  
8 
