Ground Beef Pizza: 
Submitted by: Swanson | Date Added: 6 Apr 2015 
Listed in: Pizza 
Ingredients 
1 1/2 lbs. grnd beef 
2 (8 ounce.) cans tomato sauce with mushrooms 
2 (12) pizza dough circles 
1 (16 ounce.) pkg. sliced Mozzarella cheese, torn in pcs 
1 sm. clove garlic, chopped 
1 teaspoon dry oregano leaves, crushed 
1 sm. onion and green pepper, sliced & separated into rings (or your choice of toppings) 
1/4 c. grated Parmesan cheese 

Cooking Instructions 
In skillet, brown beef and drain off excess fat: add in garlic (garlic salt may be substituted for garlic clove, 1/8 tsp. is equal to 1 clove) and oregano.  

Spread tomato sauce over pizza dough circles. Top with meat. Arrange onion and green pepper rings over meat.  

Cover with Mozzarella cheese, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 425 degrees for 15 min or possibly till crusts are done. 


