Mexican Pizzas: 
Submitted by: Lana | Date Added: 12 Feb 2015 
Listed in: Pizza 
Ingredients 
Start to Finish: 5 minutes 
Cook: 8 servings 

FOR SAUCE: 
1/4 cup salsa 
1/4 cup sour cream 

FOR PIZZA: 
4 garlic-herb wraps (or any 10-inch tortillas) 
2 cups shredded Mexican cheese blend 
1 can (16-ounce) refried black beans 
1 package (18-ounce) precooked ground beef for tacos 
1/2 red onion, diced 
2 cups shredded lettuce 
1 tomato, diced 
Nacho sliced jalapenos or sliced pickled jalapenos (optional) 

Cooking Instructions 
Set up grill for direct cooking over medium heat. Oil grate when ready to start cooking. 

In a small bowl, combine salsa and sour cream: set aside. 

Lay out 2 garlic-herb wraps: sprinkle with cheese blend. Top with remaining wraps: set aside. 

In a microwave-safe bowl, microwave refried black beans on high heat setting (100 percent power) for 4 to 6 minutes or until heated through, stirring twice. 

Using a cookie sheet, place cheese-filled wraps on hot, oiled grill. Cook for 2 minutes: turn over. Divide refried beans between cheese-filled wraps. 

Spread evenly over the tops of the pizzas, leaving a 1/2-inch border. Top beans with taco meat and onion. 

Cover grill: cook 2 minutes. Using the cookie sheet, remove pizza from grill. 

Top with lettuce and tomato: drizzle with salsa-sour cream mixture. Garnish with sliced jalapenos (optional). Serve hot. 


