Blue Cheese Pear Bite With White Chocolate: 
Submitted by: Ann | Date Added: 16 Feb 2015 
Listed in: Appetizers 
Ingredients 
Makes: 4 servings 
Cook: 8 minutes 

2 tablespoons unsalted butter 
1 pear, thinly sliced 
1/2 cup frozen chopped onions 
2 teaspoons lemon juice 
Kosher salt 
Freshly ground black pepper 
4 slices pumpernickel bread, toasted and each slice cut into quarters 
1 cup crumbled blue cheese 
1/4 cup white chocolate shavings 
Cooking Instructions 
Preheat the broiler on low. 

In a large skillet over medium high heat, add butter. When the butter has melted add the pear slices, onions, lemon juice, and a pinch each of salt and pepper. 

Cook until the pears are warmed through and soft but not falling apart, about 5 minutes. 

Place the toast squares onto a baking sheet. Lay a few slices of pears in a single layer on each toast square. 

Top each with the crumble blue cheese. Place under the broiler until the cheese begins to melt, about 1 to 2 minutes. 

Transfer to a platter, garnish each with a sprinkle of the white chocolate shavings and serve immediately. 



