Cheese Fondue: 
Submitted by: Carroll | Date Added: 13 Feb 2015 
Listed in: Appetizers 
Ingredients 
Makes: 6 servings 
Start to Finish: 20 minutes 

CHEESE FONDUE: 
1 package (8-ounce) cream cheese 
1 can (10-ounce) condensed cheddar cheese soup 
1/2 cup half-and-half 
1/2 cup shredded cheddar cheese 
Cut-up vegetables and pretzel sticks 

Cooking Instructions 
For Cheese Fondue, using a table knife, cut cream cheese into 1-inch pieces. Place in a microwave-safe bowl. Cover bowl with a paper towel. 

Microwave on medium-high for 1 1/2 minutes. Using oven mitts, remove from microwave. Remove paper towel. 

Using a wooden spoon, stir in cheddar cheese soup, the 1/2 cup half-and-half, and the cheddar cheese. Replace paper towel. Return to microwave. 

Cook on medium-high about 5 minutes or until smooth, stirring every minute. Serve with cut-up vegetables and pretzel sticks.
 

