Chicken-Bacon-Ranch Burrito: 
Submitted by: Perkins | Date Added: 3 Apr 2015 
Listed in: Calorie Counting 
Ingredients 
1 slice center-cut bacon or turkey bacon  
3 oz. raw boneless skinless chicken breast, cut into bite-sized pieces  
1 tsp. lime juice  
1/8 tsp. salt-free seasoning mix  
1 wedge The Laughing Cow Light Creamy Swiss cheese  
1/4 tsp. ranch dressing/dip seasoning mix  
1/2 oz. (about 1 tbsp.) mashed avocado  
1/2 tsp. chipotle pepper sauce  
1 medium-large high-fiber flour tortilla with 110 calories or less 
1/2 cup shredded lettuce  
1/4 cup chopped tomato  
2 tbsp. chopped onion  

Cooking Instructions 
Cook bacon until crispy, either in a skillet over medium heat or on a microwave-safe plate in the microwave. (See package for cook time.)  

Bring a skillet sprayed with nonstick spray to medium-high heat. Add chicken, and top with lime juice and salt-free seasoning. Cook and stir for about 4 minutes, until cooked through.  

To make the sauce, in a small bowl, combine ranch seasoning with cheese wedge. Stir until smooth and well mixed. Add avocado and chipotle sauce, and stir until uniform.  

Microwave tortilla on a microwave-safe plate for 15 seconds, or until warm.  

Spread sauce down the middle of the tortilla, and top with lettuce, chicken, tomato, and onion. Chop or crumble bacon, and layer over the onion.  

Wrap tortilla up by first folding in one side (to keep filling from escaping) and then tightly rolling it up from the bottom. 


START RECIPE
Melty Veggie Sandwich: 
Submitted by: Murphy | Date Added: 3 Apr 2015 
Listed in: Calorie Counting 
Ingredients 
1 portabella mushroom cap (stem removed)  
2 slices light bread  
1 oz. (about 2 tbsp.) roughly mashed avocado  
1/2 tbsp. chopped fresh cilantro  
1/2 tsp. lime juice  
Dash salt  
Dash garlic powder  
Dash onion powder  
Dash black pepper  
1 slice Sargento Reduced Fat Pepper Jack cheese 
2 medium tomato slices  
1 thin slice red onion  
1 medium lettuce leaf  
2 tsp. light whipped butter or light buttery spread 

Cooking Instructions 
Bring a skillet sprayed with nonstick spray to medium-high heat. Place mushroom cap in the skillet, rounded side down. Cover and cook until soft, about 6 minutes.  

Meanwhile, lightly toast bread. In a small bowl, combine avocado, cilantro, lime juice, and salt: mix well.  

Remove mushroom cap from the skillet, and blot to remove excess moisture. Thinly slice, and sprinkle with garlic powder, onion powder, and pepper.  

Top one slice of bread with cheese, sliced mushroom, tomato, onion, and lettuce. Spread avocado mixture on the other bread slice, and place over the stack, avocado side down. Spread the top of the sandwich with 1 tsp. butter.  

Clean skillet, if needed. Re-spray and bring to medium heat. Carefully place sandwich in the skillet, buttered side down. Spread the top with remaining 1 tsp. butter.  

Cook until bread is golden brown and cheese has melted, about 2 minutes per side, flipping carefully. 



