If you are a fan of the famous Pizookie while dining at BJ’s, you are going to love this CopyCat BJ’s Pizookie Recipe. With just a few ingredients and very little time, you can enjoy a Pizza Cookie right at home for a fraction of the cost. 

Copycat BJ's Pizookie- With just a few ingredients and very little time, you can enjoy a Pizza Cookie right at home for a fraction of the cost.Save 

COPYCAT BJ’S PIZOOKIE 
This Pizza-Cookie is one of those desserts that delivers both cuteness and yumminess. If you have never had the chance to enjoy a Pizookie or Pizza Cookie as it is sometimes called, now is the time. You can whip this tasty dessert up in no time at all, right at home. No need to rush off to an expensive resturant to enjoy this tasty dessert. 

Copycat BJ's Pizookie- With just a few ingredients and very little time, you can enjoy a Pizza Cookie right at home for a fraction of the cost.Save 
 
MY LATEST RECIPES 
Error loading player: 
Network error 
BJ’s restaurant and a few other chains serve up these delish cookie that are made in a pan. They are perfect for sharing with a small group. There is no way to eat this pan of filling cookie all by yourself. I will admit that I did make a couple of these over the weekend and I have been nibbling on the one I made for myself. It will probably last me a few more days, lol. 

Copycat BJ's Pizookie- With just a few ingredients and very little time, you can enjoy a Pizza Cookie right at home for a fraction of the cost.Save 

The ingredients that are needed for this CopyCat BJ’s Pizookie are the same ingredients you will find in any basic chocolate chip cookie recipe. You will just be making all of it in a cast iron skillet or other round baking dish. The most difficult part in making your cookie will be ing it bake, ha ha. It only bakes for a few minutes but seems like forever. The chocolate chip cookie aroma will have you craving cookie. 

Copycat BJ's Pizookie- With just a few ingredients and very little time, you can enjoy a Pizza Cookie right at home for a fraction of the cost.Save 

INGREDIENTS  
1/2 cup Butter 
1/2 cup Sugar 
1/2 cup Brown Sugar 
1 tsp Vanilla 
1 Egg 
1 1/2 cup Flour 
1/2 tsp Baking Soda 
1/4 tsp Salt 
1/2 cup Chocolate Chips 

Copycat BJ's Pizookie- With just a few ingredients and very little time, you can enjoy a Pizza Cookie right at home for a fraction of the cost.Save 

DIRECTIONS 
Preheat oven to 350. 
Place small skillet or 8? round pan over low heat and melt butter. 
Add sugar, brown sugar, beaten egg and vanilla. Mix well. 
Add flour, baking soda and salt. Mix until well blended. 
Add in chocolate chips and stir to evenly distribute. 
Bake 15-20 minutes or until golden brown. 
Allow to cool 10 minutes. 
Cut into slices and top with vanilla ice cream. 

