Boston Market Sweet Potato Casserole  
December 13, 2011 145 Comments  
Facebook37Tweet0Pin210Google+0StumbleUpon0Print Recipe 
Boston Market Sweet Potato Casserole has to be one of my favorite ways to make candied sweet potatoes. Now, if you don’t live near a Boston Market restaurant, you can either drive far or make your CopyKat recipe for these holiday favorites. 

Make your own delicious Boston Market Sweet Potato Casserole from scratch with this easy recipe. 

You don’t have to buy this sweet potato casserole from the restaurant. To make these, with a little bit of elbow grease, you can have a great-tasting sweet potato casserole any time of the year. This sweet potato recipe combines a thick oatmeal cookie–like crust, fluffy melting marshmallows, and a sweet and savory potato layer. It is hard to resist this dish. 

You are going to love the Boston Market Sweet Potato Casserole when you make it from scratch with this easy copycat recipe.  

We are going to make this whole thing from scratch. Don’t let the idea of cooking from scratch intimidate you. It is easy to do, and you can even  the video see how it is done. But if you don’t want to bake your sweet potatoes, you can buy cans of pureed sweet potatoes, both work equally well. 

Make Ahead Notes 
If you want to make this ahead of time, I suggest you bake this fully, and then reheat the 2nd day in the oven. The raw eggs in this dish make this undesirable to mix ahead 1 day and to bake the second day. 

You are going to love this copycat recipe, make your own delicious Boston Market Sweet Potato casserole from scratch.  

